9: What will I do with all this money?
13:
I hope no one takes it from me, 
seeing as I'm completely defenseless.
18:
...
Perhaps I went about this the wrong 
way.
20:
What kinda stunt are you tryin' to pull 
here?
22:
Weren't you the girl with Keira? 
What're you doin' in a place like this?
26: I came here to see you.
29:
Hah! What would the likes of you want 
with me? Were you seriously hoping to 
have your money taken?!
31:
We never finished our conversation 
regarding your desire for money.
36:
I've brought money with me, 
so please do tell.
38:
Why were you so eager to take this 
before?
42:
*sigh* Stella... You really ought to be 
more careful.
46:
And you, Addie—
I hope you have a good reason for 
being in a place like this.
54:
Why don't we have a little chat? 
Walk with me.
58:
I don't think I've ever seen you stay 
quiet for this long.
60:
At least eat something. 
The food here is not so terrible—
quite good, even.
65:
I see. I'll get straight to the point. 
Who are you handing your ill-gotten 
money to?
68: W-why do you know about that?
71:
Well, it doesn't look like you're spending 
it on yourself—even your beautiful 
hair's going to pot.
74:
Tell me, Addie. Who's making you do 
this?
76:
It's not like you'd be able to do 
something about it...
81:
Hey, now. I'd appreciate it if you gave 
me a little credit.
83:
See this emblem? 
You have my word, Addie. 
I'll do whatever must be done to see 
justice served.
91:
Damn bottle's empty! 
What's takin' that brat so long?!
92:
Good-for-nothing freeloaders... 
Think it's about time I kick 'em to the 
curb and get a new—
97: And this is the end of the line for you, as well.
99:
A Guild Knight?! 
What happened to the muscle I posted 
outside?
101:
D-don't tell me you took 'em all out on 
yer own! Aren't you s'posed to uphold 
the law or justice or somethin'?!
104:
Well, you see... 
I didn't want my fellow Guild Knights to 
see me do this.
109:
Taking helpless orphans, robbing them 
of their futures, and using them as your 
pawns... 
Absolutely despicable.
111:
You'll get your justice right here and 
now!
119:
I didn't take you for the vigilante type, 
Keira.
123:
I mean, I would've probably done the 
same thing, but still.
126:
I appreciate the sentiment. 
But I can't let the other knights see you 
with me.
131:
I must. Without an example to follow, 
the Guild Knights would fall apart.
134:
Fortunately, our commander has been 
an excellent role model for the force.
135:
It's thanks to him that 
I can do what I do.
138:
Even if they're stingy and don't let you 
do your job sometimes, huh?
141:
Ouch. There's still plenty of room for 
improvement, of course.
145:
We're here to help, Keira. 
Just give us the word.
151:
Heh... I'm starting to lose track of things 
I can't tell others about.
